LSP: 4 - The subclasses (`EmailService`, `SMSService`, `EmailClient`) correctly override the methods from their respective interfaces, which adheres to the Liskov Substitution Principle.

ISP: 2 - The `NotificationSender` and `NotificationReceiver` interfaces are not following the Interface Segregation Principle. They contain methods that are not relevant to all implementing classes, leading to unnecessary complexity.

DIP: 3 - The code does not follow the Dependency Inversion Principle. High-level modules depend on low-level modules directly, which makes it difficult to change the implementation of low-level modules without affecting high-level modules.

